The Telegraph - Calcutta
		 Sunday, January 26, 2003 				 Ramchand for allround show
																								Mumbai, Jan. 25 (PTI): Former India captain G.S. Ramchand Saturday said India will have to improve in all aspects of the game, especially bowling and fielding, if they were to advance to the World Cup semi-finals.																								Talking to reporters after former cricket board chief Raj Singh Dungarpur launched his handbook All about World Cup cricket Friday, Ramchand said: After a disastrous New Zealand tour, the boys have to really pull up their socks and improve tremendously in all departments. 
